text: Three ships of the Japanese Navy have been named Tsugaru: * was previously the Russian cruiser Pallada launched in 1899 and renamed following capture by Japan in 1908. She was stricken in 1922 and scuttled in 1924 * was a minelayer launched in 1940 and sunk in 1944 * was a minelayer launched in 1955 and converted to a cable ship 1957 Category:Japanese Navy ship names Category:Imperial Japanese Navy ship names
title: Japanese ship Tsugaru
